# Code Patterns

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router) + TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4 + shadcn/ui + Lucide React icons
- **Canvas**: React Flow (`@xyflow/react`)
- **Rich Text**: Tiptap v3
- **State**: Zustand
- **Auth + DB + Storage**: Supabase
- **AI**: Vercel AI SDK (`ai`) + OpenAI
- **Payments**: Polar.sh
- **Validation**: Zod

## File Conventions

- Pages go in `src/app/<route>/page.tsx` (App Router).
- Reusable components go in `src/components/`.
- Canvas node components go in `src/components/nodes/`.
- Zustand stores go in `src/stores/`.
- Server Actions go in the relevant `src/app/<route>/actions.ts` or a shared `src/lib/actions/`.
- Supabase client helpers go in `src/lib/supabase/`.
- Type definitions go in `src/types/`.

## Component Rules

- Use shadcn/ui components before building custom ones.
- Use Lucide React for all icons — never import from other icon libraries.
- All forms must validate with Zod schemas.
- Client components must be marked with `"use client"` only when necessary (hooks, browser APIs, interactivity). Default to Server Components.
- Use Zustand for client-side UI/canvas state. Use Supabase for all persisted data.

## AI Chat Pattern

- Use Vercel AI SDK `useChat()` for the AI Chat Node — handles streaming, message state, and abort.
- Use the direct `openai` package only server-side for Whisper transcription and Vision calls.

## Auth Pattern

- Use `@supabase/ssr` for server-side auth in middleware and Server Components.
- Protect all `/dashboard`, `/board/*`, `/settings`, `/billing` routes via middleware.
